Preheat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.For the base, mix the water biscuits, sugar and melted butter together in a bowl, then press the mixture into the base of a 25cm/10in springform cake tin.For the topping, beat the ricotta, eggs, sugar and honey together in a bowl.Fold in the crushed pistachios and golden raisins, then spoon the topping mixture onto the base.Transfer to the oven and bake for an hour, or until set and lightly golden-brown. Remove from the oven and allow to cool completely.For the sauce, place the honey and pistachios into a pan and heat gently to warm through.To serve, slice the cake into wedges, pour over the sauce and serve with thick Greek-style yoghurt.